article_title: Dublin welcomes new community health center

article_metadata.description: Federally qualified health centers most often fill a void in medically underserved areas. But in a rare step, Columbus Neighborhood Health Center will open one next month a mile northeast of the Mall at Tuttle Crossing in the wealthy suburb of Dublin. The nonprofit Columbus Neighborhood Health Center is working with another nonprofit, Syntero, to create a center that provides patients with both primary care and behavioral health services at Syntero’s current location, 299 Cramer Creek Court. The expanded center’s first day will be Sept. 10.
